1 (10) Encumbrance. – A revocation or suspension of, or any limitation on, the full
2 and unrestricted practice of social work licensed and regulated by a licensing
3 authority.
4 (11) Executive Committee. – A group of delegates elected or appointed to act on
5 behalf of, and within the powers granted to them by, the Compact and
6 Commission.
7 (12) Home state. – The member state that is the licensee's primary state of domicile.
8 (13) Impairment. – A condition that may impair a practitioner's ability to engage
9 in full and unrestricted practice as a regulated social worker without some type
10 of intervention and may include, but is not limited to, alcohol and drug
11 dependence, mental health impairment, and neurological or physical
12 impairments.
13 (14) Licensee. – An individual who currently holds a license from the state to
14 practice as a regulated social worker.
15 (15) Licensing authority. – The board or agency of a member state, or equivalent,
16 that is responsible for the licensing and regulation of regulated social workers.
17 (16) Member state. – A state, commonwealth, district, or territory of the United
18 States of America that has enacted this Compact.
19 (17) Multistate authorization to practice. – A legally authorized privilege to
20 practice, which is equivalent to a license, associated with a multistate license
21 permitting the practice of social work in a remote state.
22 (18) Multistate license. – A license to practice as a regulated social worker issued
23 by a home state licensing authority that authorizes the regulated social worker
24 to practice in all member states under multistate authorization to practice.
25 (19) Qualifying national exam. – A national licensing examination approved by the
26 Commission.
27 (20) Regulated social worker. – Any clinical, master's, or bachelor's social worker
28 licensed by a member state regardless of the title used by that member state.
29 (21) Remote state. – A member state other than the licensee's home state.
30 (22) Rule(s) or rule(s) of the Commission. – A regulation or regulation
31 promulgated by the Commission, as authorized by the Compact, that has the
32 force of law.
33 (23) Single-state license. – A social work license issued by any state that authorizes
34 practice only within the issuing state and does not include multistate
35 authorization to practice in any member state.
36 (24) Social work or social work services. – The application of social work theory,
37 knowledge, methods, ethics, and the professional use of self to restore or
38 enhance social, psychosocial, or biopsychosocial functioning of individuals,
39 couples, families, groups, organizations, and communities through the care
40 and services provided by a regulated social worker as set forth in the member
41 state's statutes and regulations in the state where the services are being
42 provided.
43 (25) State. – Any state, commonwealth, district, or territory of the United States of
44 America that regulates the practice of social work.
45 (26) Unencumbered license. – A license that authorizes a regulated social worker
46 to engage in the full and unrestricted practice of social work.
47 "§ 90B-22. State participation in Compact.
48 (a) To be eligible to participate in the Compact, a potential member state must currently
49 meet all of the following criteria:
50 (1) License and regulate the practice of social work at either the clinical, master's,
51 or bachelor's category.
