36 (c) A member state meeting the requirements of subsections (a) and (b) of this section of
37 this Compact shall designate the categories of social work licensure that are eligible for issuance
38 of a multistate license for applicants in such member state. To the extent that any member state
39 does not meet the requirements for participation in the Compact at any particular category of
40 social work licensure, such member state may choose, but is not obligated to, issue a multistate
41 license to applicants that otherwise meet the requirements of G.S. 90B-23 for issuance of a
42 multistate license in such category or categories of licensure.
43 (d) The home state may charge a fee for granting the multistate license.
44 "§ 90B-23. Social worker participation in the Compact.
45 (a) To be eligible for a multistate license under the terms and provisions of the Compact,
46 an applicant, regardless of category, must do all of the following:
47 (1) Hold or be eligible for an active, unencumbered license in the home state.
48 (2) Pay any applicable fees, including any state fee, for the multistate license.
49 (3) Submit, in connection with an application for a multistate license, fingerprints
50 or other biometric data for the purpose of obtaining criminal history record
