43 "§ 90B-24. Issuance of a multistate license.
44 (a) Upon receipt of an application for multistate license, the home state licensing
45 authority shall determine the applicant's eligibility for a multistate license in accordance with this
46 Compact.
47 (b) If such applicant is eligible pursuant to G.S. 90B-23 of this Compact, the home state
48 licensing authority shall issue a multistate license that authorizes the applicant or regulated social
49 worker to practice in all member states under a multistate authorization to practice.
