8 "§ 90B-25. Authority of Interstate Compact Commission and member state licensing
9 authorities.
10 (a) Nothing in this Compact, nor any rule of the Commission, shall be construed to limit,
11 restrict, or in any way reduce the ability of a member state to enact and enforce laws, regulations,
12 or other rules related to the practice of social work in that state, where those laws, regulations, or
13 other rules are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Compact.
14 (b) Nothing in this Compact, shall affect the requirements established by a member state
15 for the issuance of a single state license.
16 (c) Nothing in this Compact, nor any rule of the Commission, shall be construed to limit,
17 restrict, or in any way reduce the ability of a member state to take adverse action against a
18 licensee's single state license to practice social work in that state.
19 (d) Nothing in this Compact, nor any rule of the Commission, shall be construed to limit,
20 restrict, or in any way reduce the ability of a remote state to take adverse action against a
21 licensee's multistate authorization to practice in that state.
22 (e) Nothing in this Compact, nor any rule of the Commission, shall be construed to limit,
23 restrict, or in any way reduce the ability of a licensee's home state to take adverse action against
24 a licensee's multistate license based upon information provided by a remote state.
25 "§ 90B-26. Reissuance of a multistate license by a new home state.
26 (a) A licensee may hold a multistate license, issued by their home state, in only one
27 member state at any given time.
28 (b) If a licensee changes their home state by moving between two member states:
29 (1) The licensee shall immediately apply for the reissuance of their multistate
30 license in their new home state. The licensee shall pay all applicable fees and
31 notify the prior home state in accordance with the rules of the Commission.
32 (2) Upon receipt of an application to reissue a multistate license, the new home
33 state shall verify that the multistate license is active, unencumbered, and
34 eligible for reissuance under the terms of the Compact and the rules of the
35 Commission. The multistate license issued by the prior home state will be
36 deactivated and all member states notified in accordance with the applicable
37 rules adopted by the Commission.
38 (3) Prior to the reissuance of the multistate license, the new home state shall
39 conduct procedures for considering the criminal history records of the
40 licensee. Such procedures shall include the submission of fingerprints or other
41 biometric-based information by applicants for the purpose of obtaining an
42 applicant's criminal history record information from the Federal Bureau of
43 Investigation and the agency responsible for retaining that state's criminal
44 records.
45 (4) If required for initial licensure, the new home state may require completion of
46 jurisprudence requirements in the new home state.
47 (5) Notwithstanding any other provision of this Compact, if a licensee does not
48 meet the requirements set forth in this Compact for the reissuance of a
49 multistate license by the new home state, then the licensee shall be subject to
50 the new home state requirements for the issuance of a single state license in
51 that state.
