19 "§ 90B-29. Establishment of Social Work Licensure Compact Commission.
20 (a) Establishment. – The Compact member states hereby create and establish a joint
21 government agency whose membership consists of all member states that have enacted the
22 Compact known as the Social Work Licensure Compact Commission. The Commission is an
23 instrumentality of the Compact states acting jointly and not an instrumentality of any one state.
24 The Commission shall come into existence on or after the effective date of the Compact as set
25 forth in this Article.
26 (b) Membership; Voting; Meetings. – Each member state shall have and be limited to one
27 delegate selected by that member state's licensing authority. The delegate shall be either (i) a
28 current member of the state licensing authority, who is a regulated social worker or public
29 member of the state licensing authority, or (ii) an administrator of the state licensing authority or
30 their designee. The Commission shall by rule or bylaw establish a term of office for delegates
31 and may by rule or bylaw establish term limits. The Commission may recommend removal or
32 suspension of any delegate from office. The member state board shall fill any vacancy occurring
33 in the Commission within 60 days of the vacancy. Each delegate shall be entitled to one vote on
34 all matters before the Commission requiring a vote by Commission delegates.
35 A delegate shall vote in person or by such other means as provided in the bylaws. The bylaws
36 may provide for delegates to meet by telecommunication, video conference, or other means of
37 communication. The Commission shall meet at least once during each calendar year. Additional
38 meetings shall be held as set forth in the bylaws. The Commission may meet by
39 telecommunication, video conference, or other similar electronic means.
40 (c) Powers; Duties. – The Commission shall have the following powers and duties:
41 (1) Establish a code of conduct and conflict of interest policies.
42 (2) Establish the fiscal year of the Commission.
43 (3) Establish and amend rules and bylaws.
44 (4) Maintain its financial records in accordance with the bylaws.
45 (5) Meet and take such actions as are consistent with the provisions of this
46 Compact, the Commission's rules, and the bylaws.
47 (6) Maintain and certify records and information provided to a member state as
48 the authenticated business records of the Commission, and designate an agent
49 to do so on the Commission's behalf.
