1 Any laws, statutes, regulations, or other legal requirements in a member state in conflict with the
2 Compact are superseded to the extent of the conflict. All permissible agreements between the
3 Commission and the member states are binding in accordance with their terms."
4 SECTION 3. Sections 1 and 2 of this act become effective when at least seven states
5 have enacted the Social Work Licensure Compact set forth in Section 1 of this act. The North
6 Carolina Social Work Certification and Licensure Board shall report to the Revisor of Statutes
7 when the Compact set forth in Section 1 of this act has been enacted by the seven member states.
8 The remainder of this act is effective when it becomes law.
